                                 <h2>2: Three Career Episodes</h2>
                                 <p>This section is where you have to describe three independent career episodes and must be completed in the word limit of 1000-2500 words as laid down in the guidelines of the EA. Each project should clearly describe your technical skills, leadership abilities, and work ethics. Writing three different career episodes enables you to project your skills efficiently and enhances the competencies that you can cover. You must be able to reflect your competencies confidently and choose. Provide the episodes for which you have proof of evidence and raw results which you can show in case you are asked for it.</p> 
                                 <p>Make sure that the episodes are written in the first person and should focus only on your own contributions. You should more often use terms such as “I did this,” “I led the team,” “and my role was to.” The EA team is more interested to know of the tasks which you carried out yourself rather than the team in which you were working. They want to know more about your depth of knowledge, initiative, goals achieved, understanding of the changing environment, technical abilities, ability to handle problems, etc. The CDR reports it should be prepared in high-quality English with no grammatical errors, and it should be plagiarism free. Preferably they must be written in Australian English which should not be confused with British English.The CDR should also be linked to the summary statement, and each paragraph should be marked properly.</p>
                                  
